					Full Description



Pernix Group, Inc., incorporated on June 18, 2001, is a diversified contractor. The Company's segments include construction, power services and corporate operations. The construction segment includes pre-construction (pre-con) consulting services, construction management, design build and general contracting. Its markets include the United States Department of State (DOS) and other government clients and private sector commercial clients. The power services segment includes operating and maintenance of power production facilities with longer-term contracts. The Company provides its services in a range of end markets, including construction, construction management, and power operations and maintenance (O&M) services. The Corporate segment covers the indirect activities supporting the Company's construction and power activities.Construction SegmentThe Company's construction segment includes both general contracting and construction management services with pre-con consulting. The Company's general contracting services are focused on its domestic and international projects where it has developed a global network of suppliers and subcontractors. The Company provides at-risk and agency construction management services on complex facility projects in the private sector across specific market centers, including advanced manufacturing, food/beverage, biotech/pharma, healthcare, higher education and other general commercial mixed-use sectors.Power Services SegmentThe Company's power services segment includes plant engineering, procurement and construction (EPC), O&M services and build, own, operate, transfer (BOOT) capabilities. The Company focuses its service offerings on small to mid-size power plants, as well as transmission and distribution grids and underground cable installation. The Company's O&M services include maintenance and operations, engineering, on-going reliability studies, construction management, recovery/rebuild, specialty services and rehabilitation. The Company upgrades existing facilities, including the addition of new capacity or the refurbishment or replacement of outdated equipment at customer sites. The Company also provides start up and commissioning services. In addition to its O&M services and EPC, the Company implements projects through a BOOT model to enable its customers finance and manage their infrastructure projects.The power services segment operates power plants in the Republic of the Fiji Islands (Fiji) and the Republic of Vanuatu (Vanuatu). Pernix Fiji Limited is a subsidiary of the Company that conducts power service activities in Fiji. The Kinoya Power Plant consists of over three phased-in plants located near Suva, the capital of Fiji. The Vuda Power Plant, located between Nadi and Lautoka, is the diesel-fueled power plant in Fiji with an installed capacity of approximately 24.2 megawatts for a total combined installed capacity of approximately 110 megawatts. The Company also provides services for renewable power, including development, design, construction and facility O&M services for hydroelectric, solar, biomass and other renewable energy sources.

» Full Overview of PRXG.PK







